<SLUG> BC-FBN-SANDERS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS' SANDERS UNDERGOES ANKLE SURGERY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
By JOSIE KARP 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Deion Sanders underwent arthroscopic surgery on his left ankle
yesterday in Miami, the Cowboys announced. Dr. John Uribe removed a
bone spur from the cornerback's ankle.
</P>
<P>
   The injury occurred over time, Cowboys trainer Jim Maurer said.
Sanders underwent a similar operation in 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Recovery and rehabilitation time will take from four to six
weeks, Maurer said. That means Sanders could miss the beginning
portion of training camp when the team convenes in Wichita Falls in
mid-July. In three seasons with the Cowboys, Sanders has attended
training camp only once, in 1996. When he was originally signed
before the 1995 season the Cowboys were already through with
training camp and last season he played baseball while his
teammates practiced in Austin.
</P>
<P>
   The operation could hamper the plans of first-year Cowboys coach
Chan Gailey to include Sanders in the offense. Sanders has not
participated in offensive practices during off-season workouts.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
