<HEADLINE>
ONLY THE LOOK IS LIGHTER  
 (JT) 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Once June arrives, those indispensable leather tote
bags look awfully heavy. It is definitely time to switch to fabric
or straw.
</P>
<P>
   In Henri Bendel's private-label collection are natural straw
totes ($68) and woven straw totes that are lined in green or
lavender ($78).
</P>
<P>
   The A/X Armani Exchange, 568 Broadway (Prince Street), has a
two-compartment straw tote with brown leather handles ($68).
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has totes in patterned canvas, natural straw or
woven plastic by Kate Spade ($75 to $195), flower-trimmed straw
totes by Rafe ($185) and an embroidered cotton tote by CK Calvin
Klein ($48).
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has see-through mesh totes by Miu Miu ($230),
crocheted plastic bags by Tote le Monde ($145) and plaid cotton
bags by Pixie Yates ($135).
</P>
<P>
   Saks Fifth Avenue has flower-trimmed straw bags by Kate Spade
($160) and Rafe ($175), woven pink plastic by Inca ($55) and a
private-label straw with wooden handles ($100).
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
