DEMOCRATIC &LR;  _ As Boris Yeltsin's cabinet firings show, Russia's
system of checks and balances is underdeveloped, leaving the
country prone to the whims of a mercurial chief executive.
(slugged: BC-RUSSIA-NOT-DEMOCRATIC-NYTSF)
</P>
<P>
   Part III:  &UR; RUSSIA: WHAT IS TO BE DONE? &LR;  _ A new set of rules
must be established. The power of oil and gas tycoons must be
curtailed. The law making Duma members immune from prosecution
should be repealed. The large number of criminals running for Duma
seats to gain immunity is repulsive. (slugged:
BC-RUSSIA-REFORMS-NEEDED-NYTSF)
