<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Monday, June 2, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   MCDERMOTT-BOEHNER (Washington) _ House Republican Conference
Chairman John Boehner is using his dispute with Rep. Jim McDermott
as a fund-raising tool, urging potential campaign contributors to
send money to ``help me bring the Democrats to justice.''
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (Story will move in the ``w'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-CONTRIBUTE (Washington) _ Boeing, the nation's second
largest defense contractor, has vaulted into first place in a
category that really matters in Washington: campaign contributions.
The company has poured more than $1 million into federal campaign
coffers over the past 17 months, according to a study released
yesterday. The report comes as Boeing is anxiously awaiting the
upcoming debate over Most Favored Nation trade status for China,
which begins Wednesday and is expected to be ugly.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (Story will move in the ``w'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   MACARTHUR-GRANTS (Seattle) Three Seattleites win MacArthur
Foundation ``genius'' grants _ novelist Charles Johnson, poet Linda
Bierds and video artist Gary Hill. Johnson and Bierds both teach in
the creative writing program at the UW, while Hill is on the
faculty at Cornish. The foundation is announcing 29 awards Tuesday.
(already moved.)
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (story will move in the ``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Baltimore) Mariners at Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Street. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-COLUMN-VECSEY (Baltimore) Talking with M's pitcher Randy
Johnson, with the Mariners in Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-RANDY-JOHNSON (Baltimore) Latest information on the M's
Randy Johnson and the possibility of a trade.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Street. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
