  c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mellon Bank Corp., Pittsburgh, said it would buy Clair Odell
Group, Plymouth Meeting, Pa., a private property and casualty
insurance broker, for an undisclosed sum.
</P>
<P>
   Crossmann Communities Inc., Indianapolis, a builder of
single-family homes, has acquired the privately held Pinehurst
Builders Inc., Myrtle Beach, S.C., for $29.1 million in cash and
stock.
</P>
<P>
   Henry Schein Inc., Melville, N.Y., a distributor of health care
products and services, has bought Arcona Health Inc., a privately
held Canadian dental distributor, for an undisclosed amount.
</P>
