<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PROBE-SHOWDOWN-BOS </SLUG>
  
 CLINTON MOVE DESIGNED TO AVOID SHOWDOWN BEFORE sUPREME cOURT 
(For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ANN SCALES AND BOB HOHLER  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ President Clinton, in an effort to avoid a showdown
in the Supreme Court, sidestepped a fight Monday over executive
privilege to prevent two White House aides from testifying in
independent counsel Kenneth W. Starr's investigation of the Monica
S. Lewinsky matter.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, White House lawyers will prolong their battle with
Starr by pursuing Clinton's claim that his conversations with
deputy counsel Bruce R. Lindsey are shielded from Starr's inquiry
by attorney-client privilege.
</P>
