<SLUG> BC-BKC-STJOHNS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JARVIS INTERVIEWS WITH ST. JOHN'S 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Mike Jarvis of George Washington met Monday night
with Ed Manetta, St. John's athletic director, becoming the fourth
coach to interview for the Red Storm's head basketball job.
</P>
<P>
   Manetta also spoke with Davidson's Bob McKillop, Siena's Paul
Hewitt and St. Bonaventure's Jim Baron last week.
</P>
<P>
   Jarvis was on Manetta's short list two years ago when the school
hired Fran Fraschilla, but he did not interview for the job. He has
a 253-141 record in 13 seasons as a Division I head coach.
</P>
<P>
   Jarvis, who coached at Boston University for five years and the
last eight at George Washington, reportedly earned about $600,000
last year.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Storm is paying off settlements to both Fraschilla and
Brian Mahoney. Fraschilla earned $450,000 last season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-01-98 2248EDT &QL; 
