Alfonse D'Amato has been a tireless fundraiser, a politician who
works the phones with a barker's gusto. Yet since taking over the
Banking Committee in 1995, he has made his previous fundraising
seem almost pedestrian, harvesting millions of dollars from
individuals and companies in the financial industry that have a
stake in legislation that as chairman he can block with a
penstroke. By Clifford Levy.
</P>
<P>
   TENN-VALEDICTORIAN (Memphis, Tenn.) _ Three years ago, Daira
Hodges was a 14-year-old honor student. But on May 9, 1995,
everything changed when an ex-boyfriend, also 14, dragged her into
a vacant classroom, choked her, stabbed her 21 times, and then went
to take an algebra test, leaving her for dead. But she regained
consciousness, survived and on Tuesday will graduate from East High
School as valedictorian of her class. This fall, she will begin
working toward a pre-med degree at Vanderbilt.
